1
00:01:49,060 --> 00:01:54,580
=Eight Hundred=

2
00:01:57,660 --> 00:01:58,540
Grandpa, Grandma.

3
00:01:58,540 --> 00:02:00,030
(Year 1993)

4
00:02:00,030 --> 00:02:00,880
Songge.

5
00:02:00,890 --> 00:02:03,210
Please confirm if these remains
are your family members,

6
00:02:03,210 --> 00:02:04,130
Gao Peiliang

7
00:02:04,130 --> 00:02:05,260
and Liu Xiwen?

8
00:02:07,020 --> 00:02:08,170
When they left this morning,

9
00:02:08,170 --> 00:02:09,850
they were fine.

10
00:02:09,850 --> 00:02:11,500
It can't be.

11
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:12,340
That's enough, child.

12
00:02:12,850 --> 00:02:13,690
Mr. Chen,

13
00:02:14,060 --> 00:02:16,380
tell me why this happened.

14
00:02:16,380 --> 00:02:17,290
Songge,

15
00:02:17,290 --> 00:02:18,780
because of the rain,

16
00:02:18,780 --> 00:02:21,010
rocks from a landslide

17
00:02:21,010 --> 00:02:23,010
hit your grandparents' car.

18
00:02:23,010 --> 00:02:24,260
Due to excessive blood loss,

19
00:02:24,260 --> 00:02:25,500
the hospital couldn't save them.

20
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:27,380
Control yourself.

21
00:02:28,340 --> 00:02:30,260
Songge, be good.

22
00:02:30,290 --> 00:02:32,170
- Songge.
- Songge.

23
00:02:32,170 --> 00:02:33,410
- Songge.
- Don't be sad.

24
00:02:33,410 --> 00:02:34,450
It's okay, Songge.

25
00:02:36,260 --> 00:02:37,980
You're like a daughter to us.

26
00:02:37,980 --> 00:02:39,850
We will take good care of you.

27
00:02:44,850 --> 00:02:46,730
- Songge.
- Songge.

28
00:02:47,730 --> 00:02:49,170
The blood test results are out.

29
00:02:49,170 --> 00:02:50,500
(Fengyang Mine Workers' Hospital Lab Report)
Serum creatinine is already at 1,200.

30
00:02:51,130 --> 00:02:52,060
What does that mean?

31
00:02:52,820 --> 00:02:54,060
It's uremia.

32
00:02:54,060 --> 00:02:54,940
She needs dialysis.

33
00:02:57,540 --> 00:02:59,450
How can Songge

34
00:02:59,450 --> 00:03:00,660
be so pitiful?

35
00:03:00,660 --> 00:03:02,170
No family since she was little,

36
00:03:02,940 --> 00:03:04,730
and now, she has this disease.

37
00:03:04,730 --> 00:03:07,100
This disease is the most draining.

38
00:03:07,100 --> 00:03:08,100
Draining for the patient,

39
00:03:08,100 --> 00:03:09,980
draining for the family.

40
00:03:09,980 --> 00:03:11,340
If things go wrong,

41
00:03:11,340 --> 00:03:12,890
the whole family could be ruined.

42
00:03:13,820 --> 00:03:14,980
Do you know

43
00:03:14,980 --> 00:03:17,500
how much one dialysis session costs?

44
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:19,110
We have to treat her
regardless of the cost.

45
00:03:30,820 --> 00:03:34,820
=Episode 12=
(Old Coal Washing Plant)

46
00:04:45,020 --> 00:04:46,050
Hui.

47
00:04:47,610 --> 00:04:48,810
Hui!

48
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:23,020
(Public Security)

49
00:05:23,020 --> 00:05:23,860
Get out of the car.

50
00:05:27,850 --> 00:05:28,690
Director Chen.

51
00:05:30,930 --> 00:05:31,770
Where's the person?

52
00:05:32,780 --> 00:05:33,660
He ran.

53
00:06:10,850 --> 00:06:12,900
Mom, what are you still doing back here?

54
00:06:15,930 --> 00:06:17,850
What kind of birthday is this?

55
00:06:17,850 --> 00:06:19,300
Mom, I'm sorry.

56
00:06:20,140 --> 00:06:23,460
I suddenly realized I forgot the candles,
so I thought about going out to buy some.

57
00:06:23,460 --> 00:06:25,490
But I ran all over Fengyang
and couldn't find any.

58
00:06:29,340 --> 00:06:30,180
What is this?

59
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,020
Turns out I didn't forget.

60
00:06:35,610 --> 00:06:36,450
Mom,

61
00:06:36,580 --> 00:06:37,420
where's Dad?

62
00:06:38,810 --> 00:06:40,250
Same as you, acting crazy.

63
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:46,740
Mom.

64
00:07:13,130 --> 00:07:14,050
Alright, Mom.

65
00:07:14,050 --> 00:07:15,930
Don't be angry anymore, okay?

66
00:07:15,930 --> 00:07:17,250
Be happy.

67
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:21,110
We have to blow out the candles
for it to count as a birthday.

68
00:07:28,780 --> 00:07:29,620
Hui, you're back.

69
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:31,540
Dad.

70
00:07:33,140 --> 00:07:34,810
Something came up
at Director Tong's home,

71
00:07:35,410 --> 00:07:36,660
so he had me cover his shift.

72
00:07:37,850 --> 00:07:39,730
There's a lot going on
at the station now,

73
00:07:39,730 --> 00:07:41,540
and we're short-staffed,

74
00:07:41,540 --> 00:07:42,780
so that's why I'm back late.

75
00:07:44,170 --> 00:07:45,010
Don't be upset.

76
00:07:45,780 --> 00:07:46,620
Happy Birthday.

77
00:07:49,660 --> 00:07:50,500
Are you angry?

78
00:07:52,140 --> 00:07:52,980
Mom,

79
00:07:53,290 --> 00:07:54,580
since Dad is here now,

80
00:07:54,580 --> 00:07:55,580
let's light the candles.

81
00:08:09,170 --> 00:08:11,250
Dad, can you turn off the light?

82
00:08:12,220 --> 00:08:13,060
Right.

83
00:08:14,020 --> 00:08:14,860
Turn off the light.

84
00:08:16,810 --> 00:08:18,050
Turn off the light.

85
00:08:27,220 --> 00:08:28,540
You paged me just now.

86
00:08:35,650 --> 00:08:36,730
Anything?

87
00:08:48,250 --> 00:08:49,130
What's the matter?

88
00:08:50,460 --> 00:08:51,530
I'm asking if you paged me

89
00:08:51,530 --> 00:08:53,010
just now.

90
00:08:53,010 --> 00:08:53,850
Is everything okay?

91
00:08:59,420 --> 00:09:00,770
I was just asking if you were back.

92
00:09:11,370 --> 00:09:12,210
Mom,

93
00:09:12,530 --> 00:09:13,370
make a wish.

94
00:09:15,980 --> 00:09:16,820
Come on.

95
00:09:18,730 --> 00:09:20,420
What wish could I have?

96
00:09:20,420 --> 00:09:21,530
I just hope

97
00:09:21,530 --> 00:09:23,530
that our family

98
00:09:23,530 --> 00:09:24,850
can stay happy and harmonious.

99
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:29,370
Mom, our family
is certainly happy and harmonious.

100
00:09:30,850 --> 00:09:34,010
- Happy birthday to you.
- Happy birthday to you.

101
00:09:34,850 --> 00:09:41,610
- Happy birthday to you.
- Happy birthday to you.

102
00:09:41,610 --> 00:09:44,940
- I wish you would never get angry.
- I wish you would never get angry.

103
00:09:46,490 --> 00:09:47,330
Come on.

104
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:49,880
Okay.

105
00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:51,130
Happy Birthday,

106
00:09:51,130 --> 00:09:51,970
Mom!

107
00:09:54,060 --> 00:09:54,900
This is so wonderful.

108
00:09:58,100 --> 00:09:59,490
Mom, the knife.

109
00:09:59,850 --> 00:10:01,180
Okay, I'll cut it.

110
00:10:03,180 --> 00:10:05,940
(Happy Birthday, Mom)

111
00:10:06,060 --> 00:10:07,340
- Use this one.
- Alright.

112
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:10,610
Give it to Hui first.

113
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:11,460
Now, for your dad.

114
00:10:12,340 --> 00:10:13,180
Dad, you go first.

115
00:10:13,940 --> 00:10:14,780
Thank you.

116
00:10:15,510 --> 00:10:16,350
Dad.

117
00:10:16,700 --> 00:10:19,420
Hui, here's a big piece for you.

118
00:10:19,420 --> 00:10:20,260
Thanks, Mom.

119
00:10:22,820 --> 00:10:23,660
Happy Birthday.

120
00:10:27,340 --> 00:10:28,300
This cake is so soft.

121
00:10:28,300 --> 00:10:29,420
It's delicious.

122
00:10:29,980 --> 00:10:30,820
Dad,

123
00:10:31,100 --> 00:10:33,180
Songge bought this cake specially.

124
00:10:33,180 --> 00:10:34,820
It's sugar-free, so you can eat more.

125
00:10:36,940 --> 00:10:38,890
Songge is so thoughtful.

126
00:10:45,490 --> 00:10:47,180
Hui, it's about time.

127
00:10:47,180 --> 00:10:48,180
You still have a long way to go.

128
00:10:48,180 --> 00:10:49,130
You should head back now.

129
00:10:49,130 --> 00:10:50,490
It's fine, Mom.
It's your birthday today.

130
00:10:50,490 --> 00:10:51,710
I'll stay with you a bit longer.

131
00:10:51,980 --> 00:10:54,050
We've eaten the cake,
and I've made the wish.

132
00:10:54,060 --> 00:10:55,530
It's okay, come back next time.

133
00:10:55,530 --> 00:10:57,010
The main thing
is that the drive is too long.

134
00:10:58,850 --> 00:10:59,690
Alright, then.

135
00:11:00,610 --> 00:11:02,090
Mom, Dad, I'll be heading back.

136
00:11:02,610 --> 00:11:03,460
- Okay.
- Okay.

137
00:11:05,180 --> 00:11:06,180
Take it slow on the road.

138
00:11:06,180 --> 00:11:07,020
Hui,

139
00:11:08,820 --> 00:11:09,940
can I hitch a ride with you?

140
00:11:13,530 --> 00:11:15,010
Where are you going now?

141
00:11:15,010 --> 00:11:16,420
Director Tong is still at the station.

142
00:11:16,420 --> 00:11:18,300
I have to go and take over his shift.

143
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:19,580
It's just a few steps away.

144
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:21,100
Why are you making Hui drive you?

145
00:11:21,100 --> 00:11:22,370
I'm just too lazy to walk.

146
00:11:22,370 --> 00:11:24,010
What's wrong with having my son drive me?

147
00:11:24,010 --> 00:11:24,850
Is that okay?

148
00:11:27,420 --> 00:11:28,260
Of course, it's okay.

149
00:11:55,940 --> 00:11:56,780
Alright.

150
00:12:04,130 --> 00:12:04,970
Hui,

151
00:12:05,730 --> 00:12:06,580
you come inside too.

152
00:12:06,580 --> 00:12:08,100
Dad, it's getting late.

153
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:09,310
I still have to head back to the city.

154
00:12:11,010 --> 00:12:12,770
Just come on in.

155
00:12:12,770 --> 00:12:13,610
What's this about?

156
00:12:14,130 --> 00:12:15,340
You'll know once you're inside.

157
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:38,540
Dad,

158
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:40,610
why did you have me come in?

159
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:48,370
Dad, what are you doing?

160
00:12:48,940 --> 00:12:50,060
Why are you locking me up?

161
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:51,530
Dad, why?

162
00:12:51,530 --> 00:12:52,620
Why are you locking me up?

163
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:55,340
You don't know why?

164
00:12:55,770 --> 00:12:57,370
What should I know?

165
00:12:57,370 --> 00:12:58,490
You asked me for a ride,
and I brought you here,

166
00:12:58,490 --> 00:12:59,610
then you locked me up.

167
00:12:59,610 --> 00:13:00,730
You at least have to tell me why.

168
00:13:00,730 --> 00:13:01,600
What do you mean by this?

169
00:13:01,610 --> 00:13:02,770
Stop playing dumb with me!

170
00:13:03,890 --> 00:13:04,850
You know exactly

171
00:13:04,850 --> 00:13:05,730
what you've done!

172
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:18,580
(24-Hour Service. Fengyang Town
Police Station, Jiangbin Municipal PSB)

173
00:13:18,580 --> 00:13:21,260
(People's Public Security)

174
00:13:27,130 --> 00:13:27,970
Director Tong,

175
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:29,420
how is it?

176
00:13:32,490 --> 00:13:33,580
Claims to know nothing.

177
00:13:34,700 --> 00:13:35,540
Director Tong,

178
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:37,700
where are our men who were on lookout?

179
00:13:37,700 --> 00:13:39,610
When I got to the coal washing pool,
it was pitch black,

180
00:13:39,610 --> 00:13:41,700
and I didn't see
a single one of our people.

181
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:42,650
There was an emergency.

182
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:45,260
A home invasion robbery
occurred in the west of town.

183
00:13:45,820 --> 00:13:47,300
The station was shorthanded,

184
00:13:47,300 --> 00:13:48,420
so I deployed everyone there.

185
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,610
I wanted to tell you

186
00:13:50,610 --> 00:13:52,100
when we were on the phone earlier,

187
00:13:52,100 --> 00:13:53,580
but your signal was bad.

188
00:13:53,580 --> 00:13:54,850
Then, your phone was turned off.

189
00:13:54,850 --> 00:13:56,420
I couldn't get through to you at all.

190
00:13:57,340 --> 00:13:58,420
Director Tong,

191
00:13:58,420 --> 00:14:00,350
is there anything in this town
more important

192
00:14:00,370 --> 00:14:01,610
than the cough syrup case?

193
00:14:02,730 --> 00:14:04,300
Don't be so anxious.

194
00:14:04,300 --> 00:14:05,420
Regarding Hui's case,

195
00:14:05,420 --> 00:14:07,340
we need to re-examine the situation.

196
00:14:07,340 --> 00:14:09,100
We have to change
the interrogation method.

197
00:14:09,100 --> 00:14:10,100
Also,

198
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:12,300
the Bureau's decision on your recusal

199
00:14:12,300 --> 00:14:13,300
has already come in.

200
00:14:14,340 --> 00:14:16,940
While Hui is a suspect in the case,

201
00:14:16,940 --> 00:14:18,730
as a direct relative,

202
00:14:18,730 --> 00:14:20,130
you must recuse yourself.

203
00:14:20,130 --> 00:14:21,100
I'll comply.

204
00:14:21,100 --> 00:14:22,060
Go on home.

205
00:14:22,060 --> 00:14:24,580
Regardless of whether Hui did it or not,

206
00:14:24,580 --> 00:14:26,490
you are father and son.

207
00:14:26,490 --> 00:14:28,060
Things have become
too tense between you,

208
00:14:28,060 --> 00:14:29,820
so how will you face each other later?

209
00:14:30,610 --> 00:14:31,450
Director Tong,

210
00:14:32,060 --> 00:14:32,950
everything I'm doing

211
00:14:32,970 --> 00:14:34,610
is to save him, isn't it?

212
00:14:34,610 --> 00:14:36,180
Who could have thought he'd end up

213
00:14:36,180 --> 00:14:38,060
as the primary suspect?

214
00:14:38,060 --> 00:14:39,010
If he can't understand

215
00:14:39,010 --> 00:14:40,010
why I'm doing this,

216
00:14:41,770 --> 00:14:42,980
then he's a fool.

217
00:14:42,980 --> 00:14:44,100
The main issue now

218
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:45,890
is that you don't have any evidence

219
00:14:45,890 --> 00:14:48,460
proving it was actually Hui.

220
00:14:48,460 --> 00:14:49,530
Keeping him in custody

221
00:14:49,530 --> 00:14:50,610
based on mere suspicion

222
00:14:50,610 --> 00:14:52,180
is against the rules.

223
00:14:52,180 --> 00:14:53,530
Without direct evidence,

224
00:14:54,370 --> 00:14:56,010
once 24 hours have passed,

225
00:14:56,010 --> 00:14:57,940
you'll have to release him.

226
00:15:07,420 --> 00:15:08,460
Direct evidence...

227
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:13,980
Maybe I really do have some.

228
00:15:20,650 --> 00:15:21,490
Well?

229
00:15:21,940 --> 00:15:23,250
Can I go now?

230
00:15:23,250 --> 00:15:24,220
Chen Hui,

231
00:15:24,220 --> 00:15:25,340
take off your clothes.

232
00:15:25,340 --> 00:15:26,220
What do you mean?

233
00:15:27,610 --> 00:15:29,370
I've said everything I need to say.

234
00:15:29,370 --> 00:15:30,460
Why make me undress?

235
00:15:30,460 --> 00:15:32,100
Just do as you're told.

236
00:15:32,100 --> 00:15:33,610
I've cooperated with everything.

237
00:15:33,610 --> 00:15:35,420
You can't keep doing this over and over.

238
00:15:35,420 --> 00:15:36,980
This is a police station.

239
00:15:36,980 --> 00:15:38,890
We expect you to cooperate.

240
00:15:38,890 --> 00:15:40,130
Take them off.

241
00:15:40,130 --> 00:15:40,980
Come on.

242
00:15:40,980 --> 00:15:41,940
Help him.

243
00:15:41,940 --> 00:15:43,300
Please cooperate with us.

244
00:15:45,180 --> 00:15:46,020
I'll do it myself.

245
00:15:56,740 --> 00:15:58,700
(Holding Room)

246
00:16:03,530 --> 00:16:05,130
Director Tong, how's it going?

247
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:05,970
That's it.

248
00:16:06,170 --> 00:16:07,210
Let's wait for the results.

249
00:16:07,850 --> 00:16:08,690
Let's go.

250
00:16:27,340 --> 00:16:28,180
Big guy,

251
00:16:29,250 --> 00:16:31,010
be careful on the road.

252
00:16:31,010 --> 00:16:32,180
I've already called

253
00:16:32,180 --> 00:16:33,650
Liu Na and Kang Limin.

254
00:16:33,650 --> 00:16:35,690
When you get to the municipal PSB,
they'll coordinate with you.

255
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:36,590
- Okay.
- Fine.

256
00:16:42,490 --> 00:16:43,940
It's so late. Who's calling?

257
00:16:46,940 --> 00:16:48,130
Probably Songge.

258
00:16:48,820 --> 00:16:50,420
Hongbing, you answer it.

259
00:16:50,940 --> 00:16:52,250
Until the results are out,

260
00:16:52,250 --> 00:16:53,610
we can't alert the target.

261
00:16:54,130 --> 00:16:54,980
Understood.

262
00:16:58,730 --> 00:16:59,580
Hello?

263
00:16:59,580 --> 00:17:00,610
Hello, Mr. Chen.

264
00:17:00,610 --> 00:17:01,940
Is Chen Hui there?

265
00:17:01,940 --> 00:17:02,780
Songge,

266
00:17:03,850 --> 00:17:04,900
Hui...

267
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:06,330
Hui drank too much.

268
00:17:06,330 --> 00:17:07,490
He's not coming back today.

269
00:17:12,940 --> 00:17:13,810
Mr. Chen,

270
00:17:13,810 --> 00:17:16,180
there were too many people
for dialysis today.

271
00:17:16,180 --> 00:17:18,290
I couldn't make it
to Mrs. Chen's birthday.

272
00:17:18,290 --> 00:17:19,630
She isn't upset, is she?

273
00:17:19,630 --> 00:17:20,570
No.

274
00:17:20,570 --> 00:17:21,770
How could she be?

275
00:17:21,780 --> 00:17:22,660
Songge,

276
00:17:22,660 --> 00:17:24,220
just get some good rest.

277
00:17:25,620 --> 00:17:26,490
Okay.

278
00:17:26,490 --> 00:17:27,330
Goodbye, Mr. Chen.

279
00:17:27,860 --> 00:17:28,700
Goodbye.

280
00:17:34,140 --> 00:17:34,980
All right.

281
00:17:35,250 --> 00:17:36,090
Big guy,

282
00:17:36,290 --> 00:17:37,130
get moving.

283
00:17:37,770 --> 00:17:39,250
Be careful on the road.

284
00:17:39,900 --> 00:17:41,490
Right, I'll be off then.

285
00:17:41,490 --> 00:17:42,330
Okay, go on.

286
00:17:45,980 --> 00:17:46,820
Stop worrying.

287
00:17:47,620 --> 00:17:48,610
Give me the office keys.

288
00:17:48,980 --> 00:17:50,010
What for?

289
00:17:50,010 --> 00:17:51,330
To find some clothes for Chen Hui.

290
00:17:51,900 --> 00:17:52,770
It's freezing out.

291
00:17:52,770 --> 00:17:53,900
We can't let him get sick.

292
00:17:59,330 --> 00:18:00,170
Thank you.

293
00:18:56,090 --> 00:18:57,860
Your dad sent these clothes over for you.

294
00:18:59,420 --> 00:19:00,810
Do you know

295
00:19:00,810 --> 00:19:03,220
he's hurting even more
than you are right now.

296
00:19:03,220 --> 00:19:04,900
You can't blame him.

297
00:19:04,900 --> 00:19:07,490
As for what really happened,

298
00:19:07,490 --> 00:19:09,660
you know better than anyone.

299
00:19:09,660 --> 00:19:12,380
If you have something to say,
speak up now.

300
00:19:12,380 --> 00:19:14,090
It'll be better for you.

301
00:19:15,770 --> 00:19:17,290
I'm on duty at the office today.

302
00:19:17,290 --> 00:19:18,330
If you want to talk,

303
00:19:18,330 --> 00:19:19,220
just give me a shout.

304
00:19:21,180 --> 00:19:22,020
Hurry up.

305
00:19:22,420 --> 00:19:23,380
Put the clothes on.

306
00:19:23,380 --> 00:19:24,220
Don't catch a cold.

307
00:20:18,620 --> 00:20:23,100
(Jiangbin Municipal PSB)

308
00:20:26,770 --> 00:20:27,610
Limin.

309
00:20:28,330 --> 00:20:29,170
Big guy.

310
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:32,730
Officer Tang, could you please
try to hurry?

311
00:20:33,330 --> 00:20:35,030
If we don't have results
within 24 hours,

312
00:20:35,050 --> 00:20:36,480
we'll have to release him immediately.

313
00:20:37,660 --> 00:20:39,570
No problem. We'll have results by nine.

314
00:20:39,570 --> 00:20:40,420
Thank you.

315
00:20:40,420 --> 00:20:42,340
Please come with me
to handle the paperwork.

316
00:20:42,340 --> 00:20:43,250
Hurry up.

317
00:20:43,250 --> 00:20:44,140
Don't worry, Chief Liu.

318
00:20:45,050 --> 00:20:45,890
What's going on?

319
00:20:46,980 --> 00:20:48,090
Director Chen now suspects

320
00:20:48,090 --> 00:20:49,530
that the source seller

321
00:20:49,530 --> 00:20:50,770
of the cough syrup

322
00:20:50,770 --> 00:20:52,330
we've been tracking

323
00:20:52,330 --> 00:20:53,180
is Chen Hui.

324
00:20:54,250 --> 00:20:55,220
Chen Hui?

325
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:57,740
As for the specifics,

326
00:20:58,320 --> 00:21:00,370
we'll have to wait for the test results
to find out.

327
00:21:01,010 --> 00:21:02,090
How could this happen?

328
00:21:02,090 --> 00:21:03,700
What exactly went down?

329
00:21:03,700 --> 00:21:06,620
Earlier, didn't Officer Tang
detect that substance,

330
00:21:06,620 --> 00:21:08,220
whatever it was called,

331
00:21:08,220 --> 00:21:09,810
on the cough syrup bottle?

332
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:11,490
Later, following the lead,

333
00:21:11,490 --> 00:21:13,640
we found the place where it was hidden.

334
00:21:13,650 --> 00:21:16,090
It was at the Fengyang Coal Mine,
in an abandoned coal washing pool.

335
00:21:16,090 --> 00:21:17,490
Yesterday, right after Chen Hui
returned to Fengyang,

336
00:21:17,490 --> 00:21:19,180
someone went to the coal washing pool.

337
00:21:19,860 --> 00:21:21,900
So you're saying
it's not certain it's Hui yet?

338
00:21:22,860 --> 00:21:23,810
Not certain.

339
00:21:23,810 --> 00:21:25,220
By the time our men arrived,

340
00:21:25,220 --> 00:21:26,420
the person had already fled.

341
00:21:26,420 --> 00:21:28,230
But he made a mess of the scene
so that there was water

342
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:29,770
from the coal washing pool everywhere.

343
00:21:29,770 --> 00:21:30,860
If it really were Chen Hui,

344
00:21:30,860 --> 00:21:31,730
the substance

345
00:21:31,730 --> 00:21:33,330
would be detected on him.

346
00:21:36,010 --> 00:21:38,180
If Hui is the person
we've been looking for,

347
00:21:39,460 --> 00:21:41,050
the scarred woman must be...

348
00:21:52,060 --> 00:21:59,260
(Yingxiong Internet Cafe)

349
00:22:04,660 --> 00:22:05,500
Songge.

350
00:22:06,420 --> 00:22:07,810
The boss hasn't picked up yet?

351
00:22:09,980 --> 00:22:11,050
At this hour,

352
00:22:11,810 --> 00:22:13,180
he really should be up by now.

353
00:22:13,940 --> 00:22:16,010
Don't worry, he's fine.

354
00:22:16,010 --> 00:22:17,290
He's just sleeping in.

355
00:22:33,060 --> 00:22:34,290
Hello, Grandpa.

356
00:22:34,290 --> 00:22:35,530
This is Songge.

357
00:22:35,530 --> 00:22:37,290
Songge,

358
00:22:37,290 --> 00:22:39,570
when are you coming back to see me?

359
00:22:39,570 --> 00:22:41,410
I'll be back to visit you
in a couple of days.

360
00:22:42,180 --> 00:22:43,090
Grandpa,

361
00:22:43,090 --> 00:22:44,490
is Hui at home?

362
00:22:45,490 --> 00:22:46,460
You mean Hui?

363
00:22:47,290 --> 00:22:48,810
He left last night.

364
00:22:51,520 --> 00:22:52,540
Hello?

365
00:22:56,220 --> 00:22:57,060
Songge,

366
00:22:57,810 --> 00:22:58,650
what's wrong?

367
00:23:00,490 --> 00:23:01,330
Nothing.

368
00:23:03,220 --> 00:23:04,420
I'm not feeling well.

369
00:23:04,420 --> 00:23:06,010
I'm going to go back and rest for a bit.

370
00:23:06,570 --> 00:23:07,660
Are you okay?

371
00:23:08,290 --> 00:23:09,900
Why the sudden discomfort?

372
00:23:11,330 --> 00:23:12,170
How about...

373
00:23:13,900 --> 00:23:14,740
Songge.

374
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:21,540
Officer Liu.

375
00:23:34,700 --> 00:23:35,860
Officer Liu,

376
00:23:35,860 --> 00:23:37,140
you don't need to see me out.

377
00:23:37,140 --> 00:23:38,290
Go on back, thank you.

378
00:23:38,290 --> 00:23:39,530
You don't look well.

379
00:23:39,530 --> 00:23:40,490
I'll walk you back.

380
00:23:41,050 --> 00:23:42,370
No need, it's too much trouble.

381
00:23:42,620 --> 00:23:43,460
Not at all.

382
00:23:43,620 --> 00:23:45,570
I don't have anything else to do anyway.

383
00:23:47,770 --> 00:23:48,730
I'm really fine.

384
00:23:49,290 --> 00:23:50,700
I just need to sleep it off.

385
00:23:51,250 --> 00:23:52,380
I can't just leave you alone

386
00:23:52,380 --> 00:23:53,980
at home either.

387
00:23:53,980 --> 00:23:55,490
When I wasn't feeling well before,

388
00:23:55,490 --> 00:23:56,860
didn't you take care of me too?

389
00:23:57,660 --> 00:23:58,500
Let's go.

390
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:10,860
Officer Liu, please have a seat.

391
00:24:10,860 --> 00:24:12,490
Wait a moment, I'll make you some tea.

392
00:24:13,420 --> 00:24:15,460
Don't bother with that,
go get some sleep.

393
00:24:15,460 --> 00:24:16,620
I'll be fine here on my own.

394
00:24:31,380 --> 00:24:32,380
Thank you.

395
00:24:44,980 --> 00:24:46,140
Aren't you going to sleep?

396
00:24:47,090 --> 00:24:48,860
I'm suddenly not that sleepy anymore.

397
00:24:51,980 --> 00:24:53,250
Songge,

398
00:24:53,250 --> 00:24:54,530
today,

399
00:24:54,530 --> 00:24:56,090
did you call Hui?

400
00:24:57,180 --> 00:24:58,290
He hasn't been picking up.

401
00:25:00,940 --> 00:25:02,250
Is there anything

402
00:25:03,700 --> 00:25:04,860
you want to tell me?

403
00:25:06,620 --> 00:25:08,090
No.

404
00:25:08,090 --> 00:25:10,420
Officer Liu, do you
have something to tell me?

405
00:25:22,530 --> 00:25:23,370
Not for now.

406
00:26:33,010 --> 00:26:33,860
How did it go?

407
00:26:36,410 --> 00:26:37,250
Hello?

408
00:26:42,530 --> 00:26:43,370
Chen Hui,

409
00:26:48,860 --> 00:26:49,700
you're free to go.

410
00:27:57,530 --> 00:27:58,370
Hui,

411
00:27:59,090 --> 00:28:00,620
don't you dare blame your dad.

412
00:28:00,620 --> 00:28:01,810
He's a policeman.

413
00:28:01,810 --> 00:28:04,770
In this kind of situation,
he didn't have a choice, you know?

414
00:28:04,770 --> 00:28:05,610
Mr. Tong,

415
00:28:06,460 --> 00:28:07,660
please tell my dad

416
00:28:07,660 --> 00:28:09,730
to bring all my stuff
when he finishes work.

417
00:28:09,730 --> 00:28:10,770
I'll be waiting for him at home.

418
00:28:10,770 --> 00:28:13,080
(Holding Room)

419
00:28:13,090 --> 00:28:13,930
Chen Hui,

420
00:28:14,490 --> 00:28:16,180
you're an adult now.

421
00:28:16,180 --> 00:28:17,090
If there's a conflict,

422
00:28:17,090 --> 00:28:18,180
just call your dad outside

423
00:28:18,180 --> 00:28:19,290
and talk it through.

424
00:28:19,290 --> 00:28:20,530
Whatever you do,
don't start a scene at home.

425
00:28:20,530 --> 00:28:21,370
You hear me?

426
00:28:23,010 --> 00:28:24,090
This is a family matter.

427
00:28:24,770 --> 00:28:25,610
You little brat...

428
00:28:46,770 --> 00:28:47,610
Hongbing,

429
00:28:48,140 --> 00:28:49,140
you'd better be careful.

430
00:28:50,330 --> 00:28:52,860
I got the feeling just now
that Hui is in a very bad mood.

431
00:28:53,620 --> 00:28:55,050
There's a good chance

432
00:28:55,050 --> 00:28:56,720
he's going home
to complain to his mother.

433
00:29:10,250 --> 00:29:11,090
Grandpa.

434
00:29:11,860 --> 00:29:12,860
Hui, you're back.

435
00:29:13,530 --> 00:29:14,530
I came to see you.

436
00:29:16,090 --> 00:29:16,930
Grandpa,

437
00:29:17,380 --> 00:29:18,420
rest for a bit.

438
00:29:18,420 --> 00:29:20,370
Wearing the hearing aid
for too long isn't good.

439
00:29:21,620 --> 00:29:22,570
Okay.

440
00:29:23,050 --> 00:29:23,890
Come.

441
00:29:44,920 --> 00:29:45,760
Hello?

442
00:29:45,770 --> 00:29:47,170
Songge, it's me.

443
00:29:49,140 --> 00:29:50,010
Are you okay?

444
00:29:50,460 --> 00:29:52,020
Don't worry, I'm fine.

445
00:29:52,250 --> 00:29:53,140
What happened?

446
00:29:59,050 --> 00:29:59,890
Last night,

447
00:30:00,130 --> 00:30:01,490
my dad locked me up at the station.

448
00:30:03,420 --> 00:30:05,490
He's suspicious of us?

449
00:30:05,490 --> 00:30:07,140
But it's fine now.

450
00:30:07,140 --> 00:30:08,330
How are things on your end?

451
00:30:08,330 --> 00:30:09,860
Officer Liu came by early this morning.

452
00:30:10,030 --> 00:30:11,820
She was probably here
to keep an eye on me.

453
00:30:12,460 --> 00:30:14,090
But she left after getting a phone call.

454
00:30:14,620 --> 00:30:15,570
Then, everything's fine.

455
00:30:17,010 --> 00:30:19,010
Chen Hui, when are you coming back?

456
00:30:19,660 --> 00:30:20,940
Later.

457
00:30:20,940 --> 00:30:22,180
I still have one thing to do.

458
00:30:23,190 --> 00:30:24,050
At a time like this,

459
00:30:24,050 --> 00:30:25,250
what else do you have to do?

460
00:30:25,250 --> 00:30:26,720
We can't just sit and wait for death.

461
00:30:27,180 --> 00:30:28,050
I have to strike back.

462
00:30:28,070 --> 00:30:29,010
Chen Hui,

463
00:30:29,080 --> 00:30:30,220
since it's over now,

464
00:30:30,220 --> 00:30:31,220
just let it go.

465
00:30:31,220 --> 00:30:32,060
Listen to me.

466
00:30:32,280 --> 00:30:33,220
Wait for me to get back.

467
00:30:42,460 --> 00:30:43,300
Grandpa.

468
00:30:49,430 --> 00:30:50,940
Ding Yue, you bought so many groceries.

469
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:52,340
Are you heading out?

470
00:31:10,380 --> 00:31:11,220
Dad.

471
00:31:12,050 --> 00:31:12,890
Dad.

472
00:31:14,090 --> 00:31:15,090
Are you hungry?

473
00:31:15,620 --> 00:31:16,460
No.

474
00:31:17,490 --> 00:31:19,290
I brought you some soup.

475
00:31:19,290 --> 00:31:20,810
If you're hungry,

476
00:31:20,810 --> 00:31:22,330
I'll get you a piece of the cake

477
00:31:22,330 --> 00:31:24,020
that Hui bought yesterday
from the fridge.

478
00:31:24,330 --> 00:31:25,170
I'm not hungry.

479
00:31:25,900 --> 00:31:27,090
Let's wait and eat together.

480
00:31:27,090 --> 00:31:28,660
Okay, keep an eye on it then.

481
00:31:29,220 --> 00:31:30,060
Will do.

482
00:31:40,980 --> 00:31:41,820
Mom.

483
00:31:42,660 --> 00:31:43,530
Mom,

484
00:31:43,530 --> 00:31:44,770
what's wrong?

485
00:31:44,770 --> 00:31:45,700
Nothing.

486
00:31:45,700 --> 00:31:47,290
When I got up this morning,

487
00:31:47,290 --> 00:31:49,050
I tweaked my back.

488
00:31:49,050 --> 00:31:50,770
I think my herniated disc

489
00:31:50,770 --> 00:31:51,770
is acting up again.

490
00:31:52,380 --> 00:31:53,220
Stop working.

491
00:31:53,220 --> 00:31:54,570
I'll help you inside to rest.

492
00:31:54,570 --> 00:31:55,900
No need.

493
00:31:55,900 --> 00:31:56,900
I'll just sit for a bit.

494
00:31:58,460 --> 00:31:59,300
Take it easy.

495
00:32:01,900 --> 00:32:02,810
I'll get you a chair.

496
00:32:07,900 --> 00:32:08,740
Sit down slowly.

497
00:32:12,050 --> 00:32:12,890
How is it?

498
00:32:13,380 --> 00:32:14,220
It's okay.

499
00:32:16,140 --> 00:32:17,330
Why are you back again?

500
00:32:20,660 --> 00:32:21,900
I never left last night.

501
00:32:22,490 --> 00:32:24,180
You didn't leave?

502
00:32:24,180 --> 00:32:25,810
Then, why didn't you come home?

503
00:32:27,420 --> 00:32:28,380
Don't even ask, Mom.

504
00:32:29,700 --> 00:32:30,660
Just thinking about it

505
00:32:31,700 --> 00:32:33,050
makes me so angry.

506
00:32:34,140 --> 00:32:35,290
What happened now?

507
00:32:36,530 --> 00:32:38,010
It's all my dad's fault.

508
00:32:39,460 --> 00:32:40,330
Your dad?

509
00:32:42,570 --> 00:32:43,530
- Off to work?
- Chen.

510
00:32:48,810 --> 00:32:49,650
Wait.

511
00:32:58,810 --> 00:32:59,860
Is Mom at home?

512
00:33:00,700 --> 00:33:01,540
Yes.

513
00:33:03,050 --> 00:33:03,940
What did you tell her?

514
00:33:05,620 --> 00:33:06,620
I just told her

515
00:33:06,620 --> 00:33:07,860
what you did.

516
00:33:08,770 --> 00:33:10,330
Regarding last night,

517
00:33:11,460 --> 00:33:13,180
did you want to make things even worse?

518
00:33:14,490 --> 00:33:16,310
If you're so afraid of Mom knowing,

519
00:33:16,320 --> 00:33:18,180
why weren't you afraid
when you locked me up?

520
00:33:18,180 --> 00:33:19,530
I've already let you out.

521
00:33:19,530 --> 00:33:20,770
Must you come home to cause trouble?

522
00:33:20,770 --> 00:33:22,710
If you didn't mess with me,
would I mess with you?

523
00:33:23,220 --> 00:33:24,250
Why did you lock me up?

524
00:33:24,250 --> 00:33:25,090
A summons.

525
00:33:25,090 --> 00:33:26,290
A police summons lasts...

526
00:33:26,290 --> 00:33:28,050
Twelve hours for criminal cases,

527
00:33:28,050 --> 00:33:30,500
and twenty-four for complex ones, right?

528
00:33:33,420 --> 00:33:34,770
I'm asking why you locked me up.

529
00:33:34,770 --> 00:33:36,010
What was the reason?

530
00:33:36,010 --> 00:33:37,250
It's your duty to cooperate

531
00:33:37,770 --> 00:33:38,700
with a police summons.

532
00:33:39,460 --> 00:33:40,460
So, there is no reason.

533
00:33:41,420 --> 00:33:42,660
You're even too lazy to make up

534
00:33:42,660 --> 00:33:44,050
some trumped-up charges now?

535
00:33:44,050 --> 00:33:45,050
Save your grumbling.

536
00:33:45,050 --> 00:33:47,300
If you truly don't know why deep down,

537
00:33:48,090 --> 00:33:48,930
then you don't ever

538
00:33:50,510 --> 00:33:52,090
need to know for the rest of your life.

539
00:33:52,090 --> 00:33:52,980
Give me my things.

540
00:34:13,530 --> 00:34:14,370
Move.

541
00:34:40,860 --> 00:34:43,130
Look, you're keeping me here
stalling like this,

542
00:34:43,130 --> 00:34:44,860
(Liusan Mutton Restaurant)
but it doesn't solve anything.

543
00:34:44,860 --> 00:34:46,090
It's the middle of the night.

544
00:34:46,090 --> 00:34:46,940
Aren't you going home?

545
00:34:48,050 --> 00:34:49,260
If you keep stalling,

546
00:34:49,260 --> 00:34:50,490
I can't stay with you anymore.

547
00:34:52,260 --> 00:34:54,090
I haven't figured out yet

548
00:34:54,090 --> 00:34:56,050
how to explain this to Ding Yue.

549
00:34:56,050 --> 00:34:56,900
Anyway, I think

550
00:34:58,860 --> 00:35:00,860
you might really be wrong this time.

551
00:35:00,860 --> 00:35:02,340
If the person who ran away

552
00:35:02,340 --> 00:35:03,460
from the coal washing plant

553
00:35:03,460 --> 00:35:05,490
really was Hui,

554
00:35:05,490 --> 00:35:06,690
not a single drop of water

555
00:35:06,690 --> 00:35:08,490
from the pool got on him.

556
00:35:09,090 --> 00:35:10,170
Is that even possible?

557
00:35:10,170 --> 00:35:13,210
I'm relying on my instincts
from all my years as a cop.

558
00:35:13,900 --> 00:35:15,340
Could it be such a coincidence?

559
00:35:15,340 --> 00:35:16,740
We've been here for years

560
00:35:16,740 --> 00:35:18,860
and handled many cases, big and small,

561
00:35:18,860 --> 00:35:19,700
but never once

562
00:35:19,700 --> 00:35:21,780
has a case been as strange as this.

563
00:35:22,420 --> 00:35:23,780
- Right?
- Enough.

564
00:35:24,340 --> 00:35:26,210
"Big and small cases"...

565
00:35:26,210 --> 00:35:27,490
What kind of big cases

566
00:35:27,490 --> 00:35:28,570
could we have here?

567
00:35:28,570 --> 00:35:30,050
At most, it's brawls,

568
00:35:30,050 --> 00:35:31,650
robberies, thefts,

569
00:35:31,660 --> 00:35:32,730
or unlicensed mining.

570
00:35:33,170 --> 00:35:34,690
Since I became Director,

571
00:35:34,690 --> 00:35:35,740
the biggest case

572
00:35:35,740 --> 00:35:36,860
involved someone

573
00:35:36,860 --> 00:35:38,820
stealing over 400 kg of scrap iron.

574
00:35:41,490 --> 00:35:42,340
Don't forget,

575
00:35:43,380 --> 00:35:44,220
we're the ones

576
00:35:44,230 --> 00:35:45,820
who vowed to the entire city

577
00:35:45,820 --> 00:35:47,010
to get this done.

578
00:35:47,740 --> 00:35:48,940
Isn't the cough syrup case

579
00:35:48,940 --> 00:35:50,210
the biggest

580
00:35:50,210 --> 00:35:51,380
we have right now?

581
00:35:51,380 --> 00:35:53,340
So, this is an opponent

582
00:35:53,340 --> 00:35:55,530
we've never encountered before.

583
00:35:56,610 --> 00:35:58,300
Making a misjudgment

584
00:36:00,050 --> 00:36:01,420
is allowed, okay?

585
00:36:06,090 --> 00:36:07,780
I really do hope

586
00:36:07,780 --> 00:36:08,820
that I'm wrong.

587
00:36:11,170 --> 00:36:12,010
Come on.

588
00:36:12,300 --> 00:36:13,650
Finish your drink and go home.

589
00:36:41,260 --> 00:36:42,100
You're back.

590
00:36:47,170 --> 00:36:48,460
Why are you sleeping here?

591
00:36:49,010 --> 00:36:50,010
Waiting for you.

592
00:36:50,010 --> 00:36:51,380
I fell asleep while waiting.

593
00:36:53,090 --> 00:36:54,010
What's wrong?

594
00:36:54,010 --> 00:36:55,010
It's my back.

595
00:36:55,010 --> 00:36:56,260
I tweaked it today.

596
00:36:56,260 --> 00:36:57,580
Then, don't move. Don't move.

597
00:36:57,780 --> 00:36:59,170
Let me.

598
00:36:59,620 --> 00:37:00,610
- Let me see.
- It's fine.

599
00:37:00,610 --> 00:37:01,450
It's fine.

600
00:37:01,690 --> 00:37:02,530
Is it serious?

601
00:37:02,550 --> 00:37:03,430
Right here?

602
00:37:04,010 --> 00:37:05,090
Or here on the right?

603
00:37:12,210 --> 00:37:14,050
Hui told you

604
00:37:15,570 --> 00:37:16,780
about what happened last night?

605
00:37:18,170 --> 00:37:19,690
You have the nerve to bring it up?

606
00:37:20,050 --> 00:37:21,090
Be a little gentler.

607
00:37:24,780 --> 00:37:25,620
Alright.

608
00:37:26,170 --> 00:37:27,530
You're not feeling well.

609
00:37:27,530 --> 00:37:28,530
Once you've rested,

610
00:37:29,390 --> 00:37:30,780
I'll explain it to you.

611
00:37:32,690 --> 00:37:34,010
It's my fault.

612
00:37:34,010 --> 00:37:35,530
I didn't get a chance to tell you.

613
00:37:37,570 --> 00:37:38,740
What's with you today?

614
00:37:40,090 --> 00:37:41,050
Usually,

615
00:37:41,050 --> 00:37:42,980
you're the tough guy
who only acts out at home.

616
00:37:42,980 --> 00:37:45,010
Why are you so unusual today?

617
00:37:45,010 --> 00:37:46,050
I'm just afraid...

618
00:37:47,690 --> 00:37:48,980
I'm worried about you.

619
00:37:50,420 --> 00:37:51,860
So now you're afraid of worrying me.

620
00:37:53,050 --> 00:37:54,860
But what you and Tong did

621
00:37:54,860 --> 00:37:56,570
wasn't very honorable.

622
00:37:56,570 --> 00:37:57,980
You really put Hui through a lot.

623
00:37:59,260 --> 00:38:00,740
Yes.

624
00:38:02,260 --> 00:38:03,340
We were inconsiderate.

625
00:38:04,420 --> 00:38:05,610
Then again,

626
00:38:05,610 --> 00:38:06,570
anyway, this matter

627
00:38:06,570 --> 00:38:08,170
has nothing to do with us.

628
00:38:08,170 --> 00:38:09,010
Let's go.

629
00:38:09,020 --> 00:38:10,090
Go upstairs to bed.

630
00:38:10,090 --> 00:38:10,930
Go to sleep?

631
00:38:13,420 --> 00:38:14,460
Is that it?

632
00:38:15,820 --> 00:38:17,110
What else should we do but sleep?

633
00:38:20,380 --> 00:38:21,460
Don't you have anything else

634
00:38:21,460 --> 00:38:22,380
to say to me?

635
00:38:23,340 --> 00:38:24,820
My back is hurting like crazy.

636
00:38:24,820 --> 00:38:25,780
I don't have the energy

637
00:38:25,780 --> 00:38:26,630
to talk to you.

638
00:38:26,640 --> 00:38:27,640
Go upstairs. Let's go.

639
00:38:29,530 --> 00:38:30,370
No.

640
00:38:30,940 --> 00:38:32,860
What exactly did Hui tell you?

641
00:38:32,860 --> 00:38:34,860
Why are you being so persistent?

642
00:38:35,530 --> 00:38:37,010
He just told me

643
00:38:37,010 --> 00:38:39,170
you insisted he
transfer the roller skating rink

644
00:38:39,170 --> 00:38:40,610
to Tong's niece.

645
00:38:41,340 --> 00:38:42,570
The classmate of his,

646
00:38:42,570 --> 00:38:44,820
the one selling TVs
at the department store...

647
00:38:44,820 --> 00:38:46,260
What was his name again?

648
00:38:47,170 --> 00:38:48,530
- Wang Xiaojian.
- Right.

649
00:38:48,530 --> 00:38:49,820
It's Wang Xiaojian.

650
00:38:49,820 --> 00:38:52,050
He also wanted
to take over the roller skating rink.

651
00:38:52,050 --> 00:38:54,380
Didn't they run
into each other on the street?

652
00:38:54,380 --> 00:38:55,650
He blamed Hui,

653
00:38:55,650 --> 00:38:58,010
made Hui treat him to a meal,
and made him drink as a penalty.

654
00:38:58,010 --> 00:38:58,900
It lasted all night.

655
00:38:58,900 --> 00:39:00,090
He threw up several times.

656
00:39:02,940 --> 00:39:03,780
When did

657
00:39:05,490 --> 00:39:07,210
Hui tell you this?

658
00:39:07,210 --> 00:39:08,420
At noon today.

659
00:39:08,900 --> 00:39:10,130
He only told you that?

660
00:39:11,860 --> 00:39:13,610
Then, what else should he have told me?

661
00:39:15,430 --> 00:39:16,910
He shouldn't have said anything else.

662
00:39:17,980 --> 00:39:19,300
He's telling the truth.

663
00:39:19,900 --> 00:39:20,740
Let's go.

664
00:39:45,650 --> 00:39:46,490
Chen Hui.

665
00:39:49,380 --> 00:39:50,220
Chen Hui.

666
00:39:53,530 --> 00:39:54,740
When did you get up?

667
00:39:58,380 --> 00:39:59,530
I haven't been able to sleep.

668
00:40:03,340 --> 00:40:05,170
The fact that Mr. Chen let you go

669
00:40:05,170 --> 00:40:06,530
means he has no evidence.

670
00:40:07,650 --> 00:40:09,530
Besides, we won't be doing this anymore.

671
00:40:09,530 --> 00:40:10,530
Don't overthink it.

672
00:40:10,530 --> 00:40:11,620
Come and sleep for a while.

673
00:40:14,130 --> 00:40:16,090
I originally wanted to tell
my mom about this.

674
00:40:18,300 --> 00:40:19,940
Only by making my mom worry

675
00:40:20,620 --> 00:40:21,940
would my dad's mind be unsettled.

676
00:40:22,820 --> 00:40:24,690
But when I saw
my mom's back hurting like that,

677
00:40:26,210 --> 00:40:28,040
I couldn't bear to make her worry.

678
00:40:31,900 --> 00:40:33,300
I just suddenly felt

679
00:40:35,740 --> 00:40:37,050
like my mom had grown old.

680
00:40:40,380 --> 00:40:41,480
I couldn't say a single word

681
00:40:42,940 --> 00:40:44,090
of what I had planned to say.

682
00:41:31,340 --> 00:41:37,460
♪I always thought
once we see the full picture♪

683
00:41:38,780 --> 00:41:44,580
♪We could understand
each other with empathy♪

684
00:41:46,180 --> 00:41:52,620
♪I always thought
the path we never took♪

685
00:41:53,340 --> 00:41:58,940
♪Must have had more beautiful scenery♪

686
00:42:00,780 --> 00:42:04,140
♪Keep moving forward
and don't look back♪

687
00:42:04,500 --> 00:42:07,740
♪The shore is only reached
by the road ahead♪

688
00:42:08,140 --> 00:42:10,980
♪Too much debt has accumulated♪

689
00:42:11,900 --> 00:42:14,780
♪In this short life♪

690
00:42:15,540 --> 00:42:19,220
♪Between right and wrong,
how to choose?♪

691
00:42:19,300 --> 00:42:22,780
♪Regret is inevitable in the end♪

692
00:42:22,940 --> 00:42:29,580
♪Even so-called love
is repaid with pain♪

693
00:42:30,060 --> 00:42:34,020
♪I hear the laughter
and follow the crowd♪

694
00:42:34,220 --> 00:42:37,420
♪Into the streets and alleys♪

695
00:42:37,700 --> 00:42:44,540
♪On that brightly lit night♪

696
00:42:45,260 --> 00:42:48,820
♪Unfortunately, the breeze in town♪

697
00:42:49,020 --> 00:42:52,540
♪Can no longer catch up to the children♪

698
00:42:52,540 --> 00:42:55,700
♪Times have changed♪

699
00:42:56,100 --> 00:42:58,500
♪Now, everything♪

700
00:42:59,180 --> 00:43:03,340
♪Is no longer what it used to be♪
